SOUTH Africa brace yourself for a MASSIVE celebration on Friday. The clock is ticking fast before a new chapter is written... in honour of South Africa. For the first time in the history of African football, the country will have a Confederation of African Football (Caf) president in Patrice Motsepe. Here we share with you the secrets that convinced Jacques Anouma, Augustin Senghor and Ahmed Yahya to rally behind him and withdraw their candidacy. But more importantly, the man behind Motsepe's successful campaign. 